abstract:
The $f^+$ form factors of the $B	o \pi$, $D	o \pi$ and $D	o K$ transitions are calculated from QCD light-cone sum rules (LCSR) and used to predict the widths and differential distributions of the exclusive semileptonic decays $B	o \pi  ar{l}
u_l$, $D 	o\pi  ar{l}
u_l$ and $D 	o K  ar{l}
u_l$, where $l=e,\mu$. The current theoretical uncertainties are estimated. The LCSR results are found to agree with the results of lattice QCD calculations and with experimental data on exclusive semileptonic D decays. Comparison of the LCSR prediction on $B	o \pi  ar{l} 
u_l$ with the CLEO measurement yields a value of |V_{ub}| in agreement with other determinations.
